{
  "texts": [
    "Let us consider an LLM f θ, which maps a prompt x to a distribution of responses P θ (y|x).",
    "We finetune this model on a dataset D = {(x i, s i)} 1≤i≤N with a loss function (x i,s i)∈D L(f θ (x i), s i), where s i represents the supervision associated with x i.",
    "Depending on the choice of L, this can represent SFT (where s i is a a target response) or RL finetuning (where s i is a reward function).",
    "While the optimal behavior that an LLM can learn during finetuning is to output the groundtruth answer to each query, this may not happen in practice for all finetuning examples.",
    "For familiar finetuning examples, the pretrained model's representations often encode useful associations between queries and responses, facilitating the finetuning optimization for those examples."
  ]
}